---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="CSV to Nested JSON Workflow for Developers"
  description="Plan how to convert CSV columns into nested JSON structures for API payloads, imports, and developer handoffs. Includes safe browser-based JSON tool links."
>
  <main class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <nav class="mb-8 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-brand-600">Home</a>
      <span class="mx-2">/</span>
      <span>CSV to Nested JSON</span>
    </nav>

    <section class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm dark:border-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-900 sm:p-8">
      <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-brand-600 dark:text-brand-400">Developer workflow</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-white sm:text-4xl">
        CSV to Nested JSON Workflow
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base leading-7 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
        CSV files are flat, but API payloads often need nested objects. Use this workflow to decide how columns should map before you convert, format, validate, and hand off JSON to another developer.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="/tools/csv-to-json" class="rounded-xl bg-brand-600 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-bold text-white hover:bg-brand-700">Open CSV to JSON Converter</a>
        <a href="/tools/json-formatter" class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-bold text-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:border-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300 dark:hover:bg-gray-800">Format JSON Output</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 dark:border-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-900">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">1. Name nested paths</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Use predictable column names such as <code class="rounded bg-gray-100 px-1 dark:bg-gray-800">user.name</code>, <code class="rounded bg-gray-100 px-1 dark:bg-gray-800">user.email</code>, and <code class="rounded bg-gray-100 px-1 dark:bg-gray-800">company.id</code> before conversion.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 dark:border-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-900">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">2. Convert flat rows</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Convert CSV to JSON first, then inspect whether the result should remain an array of objects or be transformed into grouped nested payloads.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 dark:border-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-900">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">3. Validate before upload</h2>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
          Format and validate the JSON before importing it into a database, API client, webhook, or internal admin tool.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
